Red blood cells are structurally and functionally specialized to transport oxygen from the lungs to other tissues. Their cytoplasm contains the 33% solution of oxygen-binding protein hemoglobin the O2 carrying protein that account for their acidophilia.About 1/3 of the erythrocyte mass is hemoglobin.he primary function of blood is to supply oxygen and nutrients as well as constitutional elements to tissues and to remove waste products. Blood also enables hormones and other substances to be transported between tissues and organs.
